channel.title: Fast Food
channel.description: I recently participated in a discussion about Fast Food being terribly bad for you with weight and all. I think it was a stupid discussion but i thought it would be interesting to share with you here. I think fast food is fine, but when extremely-obese (fat) people order waaay too much, it could affect you weight.

item.title: Fast Food
item.dc:creator: @srt8 srt8
item.description:
@srt8 wrote:

Any food in excess can be bad for you and make you gain weight. Of course, fast food is prepared in vats of lard…which i’m sure most of us don’t use at home but still…there are good choices that you can make with fast food. Just because someone has a McDonalds bag in their hands doesn’t mean they ordered 2 big macs and a super size fry and drink, they could have a salad and water for all we know.

Speaking of Super Sized…have you guys ever seen that movie? Now that’s crazy

item.title: Fast Food
item.dc:creator: @davidude36 Brolapse
item.description:
@davidude36 wrote:

Everything is fine in moderation I believe.

Even eating too much fruit could lead to bad consequences and this is why we must balance our diet. If we do not balance our diet we will have consequences, e.g. eating to much gets you fat, eating too little gets you anorexic. By eating the right amount you can stay a perfect size.

That’s all there is to say really. I’d say if you are over 18 your body can easily take junk food once a week or less as long as you are eating okay food the rest of the time.
